  "confidenceNotes": "All 15 headwords are attested in at least two independent sources. Question words (ninu, nanu, nukarin, kapilan, obakit, makananu, magkanu, kaninu, isanu, kumusta) are confirmed in Wikipedia's Kapampangan language article and HandWiki. Demonstrative pronouns (iyan, ita) and locatives (keni, karin, oyan) are confirmed in the Wikipedia article and the drakieness/bryanquiroz22 grammar guides which draw on scholarly Kapampangan grammar references. The spelling 'nukarin' (vs older 'nokarin') follows Wikipedia and HandWiki. 'Obakit' is confirmed in Wikipedia; the shorter form 'obat' also exists in formal registers. 'Isanu' (also 'isnanu') is confirmed in Wikipedia. 'Kumusta' is confirmed in Wikipedia, Wikivoyage, and tagaloglang.com. No entry overlaps with the AVOID-LIST."
